# Creator of Python
Python is very old language and it is a very simple language to start with. Python is a high-level language as English written language.
It is designed by a dutch programmer "Guido van Rossum" in 1990[According to Wikipedia].
For more information please visit the below mentioned link.
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)

# Python Installation
You can download python installer from the  official site "https://www.python.org/downloads/"

# Which Python version(2 or 3) should I installed? 
This is a typical question comes when you start the learning of Python programming that which Python version should I installed.
This is based on the choice and on the requirement of your projects. If you want to learn Python then there is no big difference 
for you start with any of the mentioned verion. I will explain the difference between these two versions in the next point.

# Difference between Python version 2 and 3
All the difference between these two versions are mentioned in the document
https://wiki.python.org/moin/Python2orPython3#Should_I_use_Python_2_or_Python_3_for_my_development_activity.3F

# What is new in Python 3.0
If you want to know the details of improvement and new functionality in Python 3.0 then please visit the document created by Guido van Rossum.
https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.0.html



